<paragraph blockId="17.[826,1441,449,808]" pageId="17" pageNumber="714">
<emphasis box="[826,949,450,471]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="714">Puparium:</emphasis>
Anterodorsal margin of mesothorax with enlarged setae, not spicules. Dorsal vestiture of abdomen spread across folds and not strongly confined to medial transverse bands although shorter in front and behind. Crochets translucent with dark red tips. Posterior breathing tube dark brown, long almost as long as puparium is wide with AP about 0.8¥ as long as TR is wide, coriaceous and faintly punctate and tapering sharply to about 0.5¥ of width of TR (
<figureCitation box="[911,992,725,747]" captionStart="Figures 58–61" captionStartId="49.[164,254,1145,1164]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,195,1115]" captionTargetId="figure-0@49.[323,1283,195,1115]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="Figures 58–61. Puparia of Copestylum, scanning electron photomicrographs, scales as indicated on images, 58, 59, Copestylum spinigera; 58, posterior breathing tube (prp), dorsal view width at TR = 0.87 mm; 59, prp, apical view width = 0.8 mm; 60, Copestylum cockerelli, prp dorsal view width at TR = 1.5 mm; 61, Copestylum hambletoni, prp, dorsal view width at TR = 1.45 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443512" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443512/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="714">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
). Pupal spiracles short, about 0.7¥ as long as AP and about 1.4¥ as wide apart as a pupal spiracle is long (
<figureCitation box="[1020,1150,786,808]" captionStart="Figures 54–57" captionStartId="48.[144,234,1180,1199]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,195,1148]" captionTargetId="figure-0@48.[303,1263,195,1150]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="Figures 54–57. Puparia of Copestylum, scanning electron photomicrographs, scales as indicated on images, 54, Copestylum pictum, dorsum of prothoracic shield length 3.5 mm; 55, Copestylum spinigera, pupal spiracles, ventral view length 1.12 mm; 56, 57, Copestylum hambletoni, pupal spiracle length 1.3 mm; 56, ventral view; 57, dorsal view. af, apex of anterior fold with spicules; as, anterior spiracle; lf, longitudinal fold; s, spicule groups on anterodorsal margins of mesothorax and metathorax; P, prothorax; Ms, mesothorax; Mt, metathorax." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443510" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443510/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="714">Figs 56, 57</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
