</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[826,1441,1093,1238]" pageId="17" pageNumber="714">
<emphasis box="[826,1024,1094,1115]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="714">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
The puparium of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fluke" baseAuthorityYear="1951" box="[1246,1410,1093,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="714" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hambletoni">
<emphasis box="[1246,1410,1093,1115]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="714">C. hambletoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from other Scutellatum group species considered here by the long posterior breathing tube with its sharply tapering AP and the crochets on the prolegs, which have dark red tips.
</paragraph>
